answer: Web of Science subjects are categorized under main categories such as Science and Technology, Social Sciences, and Arts and Humanities, with each of these encompassing multiple subject-specific categories (e.g., Science and Technology includes Acoustics, Electrochemistry, Literature, Physics, and Condensed Matter; Social Sciences includes Cardiac & Cardiovascular Systems, Folklore, Medicine, Research & Experimental, Cell Biology, and Food Science & Technology; Arts and Humanities includes Arabic Citation Index, Emergency Medicine, Literature, African, Australian, Canadian, and Multidisciplinary).
